**Methodologies:**
The document describes a series of studies evaluating psychological threats related to COVID-19 and their implications on various behaviors. It utilizes a confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) to validate a two-factor model distinguishing between symbolic and realistic threats related to COVID-19. The studies employed various scales including the integrated COVID-19 Threat Scale, CDC guideline adherence scale, and others measuring public health initiative support and social identity affirming behaviors.

